  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is discussed throughout the assessment narrative and applied to selected operating points; however, not all validation results carry formal UQ artifact links. Full 13-factor assessment covering software quality, numerical verification, discretization error, test conditions, output comparison, QoI relevance, validation relevance, solver error, use error, model form, model inputs, test samples, and input parameter equivalency. Decision: Accepted based on aggregate credibility evidence.",
